These are my personal SlackBuild scripts that differ from those found on SlackBuilds.org

I am in no way affiliated with slackbuilds.org, nor are any of my scripts affiliated with them. Please do not ask them for help with my scripts. I AM SERIOUS, I AM NOT AFFILITATED WITH THEM!

Some of these are forked and modified from existing build scripts.  The original author(s) will most likely not support these forked versions.

If you are familiar with the traditional SlackBuilds found off SlackBuilds.org, you will notice that my scripts are not only different, but better.  Yes, that is right, my scripts are better!

My scripts do not require you to download the source file, if you do not already have it in $CWD the script will not only download it for you, but it will verify the download with a MD5 or SHA1 hash.  I do not, nor do I ever plan on hosting other peoples source code, which is why I have my scripts auto download the source files if you do not have them.  Some of my scripts pull directly from git or svn.

If you do not know how to use a SlackBuild file, please read my HOWTO file.

